Tension remains high after two people were allegedly shot dead by KDF soldiers in Turbo Sub County. [Patrick Kibet, Standard]  Two people have allegedly been shot dead by Kenya Defence Forces –KDF soldiers in Chebarus, Turbo sub-county after a confrontation between residents and the soldiers.  The incident happened when irate residents confronted the soldiers who were on a mission to demarcate a disputed parcel of land.    The incident also left two people including a minor, nursing injuries. Residents of Turbo Sub-County gather in groups after two people were allegedly shot dead by KDF soldiers following a land dispute. [Patrick Kibet, Standard]  According to Julius Kitur a local leader, the community has been embroiled in a legal tussle with KDF over boundaries.  The community moved to court which issued orders stopping KDF from illegally exercising the land pending the determination of the court case.  More to Follow...        By Peterson Githaiga | 4 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 5 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 17 hours ago By Lynn Kolongei | 1 day ago